Joggers and pet lovers have been asking if they can jog or walk their dogs during the lockdown, well government says it's a big no. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Police Minister Bheki Cele says that dog walking and jogging won't be allowed during the 21-day lockdown. Cele comments come after Health Minister Zweli Mkhize had said that citizens would be allowed to jog and take their dogs for a walk during the period. READ: COVID-19: Services and businesses exempted from lockdown However, the police minister has provided clarity on the matter and sternly warned that jogging and dog walking is strictly prohibited. "There is no need to be on the road, there is no need to move around," Cele said. READ: SA lockdown: Brace for strict enforcement South Africans will spend the next 21 days at home from Friday in a bid to fight the spread of the coronavirus. The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in South Africa has climbed to 709.